The All Progressives Congress Thursday reacted to the threat by the candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, to challenge the outcome of Saturday’s presidential election in Court. The election was won by President Muhammadu Buhari, candidate of the APC. The National Chairman of APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, said at a press conference in Abuja on Thursday that the party was looking forward to meeting Atiku in Court. “We hope or we are looking forward to meeting Atiku in court and the facts will be laid bare,” Oshiomhole said. The press conference is currently ongoing. Details later…